By Leonard Klady 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Romero, meanwhile, joins forces with director Dario Argento to update two 
vintage Edgar Allan Poe tales next month, also in Pittsburgh. Romero's segment, 
"The Facts in the Case of M. Valdemar," casts Adrienne Barbeau as the wife of 
an insanely jealous man, while Argento reworks "The Black Cat," with a news 
reporter as the feline-phobe. Leonard Klady 
</P>
